-- $TIRI
--[[
Flute tests for Picture PNG decoding.

This technique uses pre-computed checksums from PNG images, captured from a 'good' state.  If a checksum doesn't
match, the test will fail and the decoded image will be saved to "temp:picture_test_results/".  Check the
corresponding image file, if it is acceptable then update the old checksum from the test output in order to pass
future tests.

Where possible, the test-files are 32x32 bits icons. This results in a still reasonable size of the suite even
with a large number of tests. The name of each test-file reflects the type in the following way:

    filename:                               g04i2c08.png
                                            || ||||
    test feature (in this case gamma) ------+| ||||
    parameter of test (here gamma-value) ----+ ||||
    interlaced or non-interlaced --------------+|||
    colour-type (numerical) --------------------+||
    colour-type (descriptive) -------------------+|
    bit-depth ------------------------------------+

Colour-type

* 0g - grayscale
* 2c - rgb colour
* 3p - paletted
* 4a - grayscale + alpha channel
* 6a - rgb colour + alpha channel

Bit-depth:

01 - with colour-type 0, 3
02 - with colour-type 0, 3
04 - with colour-type 0, 3
08 - with colour-type 0, 2, 3, 4, 6
16 - with colour-type 0, 2, 4, 6

Interlacing:

n - non-interlaced
i - interlaced
--]]

   include 'picture'

glResultFolder <const> = 'temp:picture_test_results/'

